TestHandledFlagFalseWhenRecoveryFails
/ When the recovery body throws, the original error propagates with the recovery error chained. The outermost handler catches the propagated error; afterward we assert the recovery error appended to %!callStack.Audit% (both errors logged).
- throw error "outer-boom", on error throw error "recovery-failure"
- on error set %finalCaught% = true
- assert %finalCaught% is true
- set %auditCount% = %!callStack.Audit.Count%
- assert %auditCount% is greater than 1
